		"notes": "\n\t<p><i>These 9-foot-tall, shaggy, yak-headed humanoids dwell in deep, hidden valleys in the highest, most inaccessible mountain ranges. They are notorious sorcerers and slavers. </i></p>\n\t<p></p>\n\t<p><strong>AC</strong> 13, <strong>HP</strong> 34, <strong>ATK</strong> 2 staff +5 (1d10) or 1 spell +6, <strong>MV</strong> near, <strong>S</strong> +3, <strong>D</strong> +0, <strong>C</strong> +3, <strong>I</strong> +3, <strong>W</strong> +2, <strong>Ch</strong> +2, <strong>AL</strong> <strong>C</strong>, <strong>LV</strong> 7</p><p></p>\n\t<p><strong> Enslave</strong>. In place of attacks, 1 target within close. Contested CHA check. If yak-folk wins, it controls target for 1d4 days. Can only enslave 1 creature at a time.</p><p></p><p><strong>Hold (INT Spell)</strong>. DC 12. Focus. One target within double near paralyzed for duration.</p><p></p><p><strong>Possession (INT Spell)</strong>. DC 14. Focus. Yak-folk transforms into mist and possesses a humanoid within near, gaining control of body and memories for duration.</p><p></p><p><strong>Wind-walk (INT Spell)</strong>. Self. DC 13. Fly double near for 5 rounds.</p><p></p>",
